I have created the Input Field developer guide at `generated/input-field.md`. The document provides comprehensive coverage of the `Dali::Ui::InputField` control for application developers using dali-ui.

The guide includes:
- **Creating an Input Field** - Basic instantiation and fluent configuration
- **Text and Placeholder** - Setting text, placeholder, alignment, and overflow handling
- **Cursor Configuration** - Cursor appearance, blinking, position, and handle images
- **Text Selection** - Programmatic selection, selection handles, and text handles
- **Password Input** - Password modes, mask characters, and reveal duration
- **Font Styling** - Font family, size, weight, width, slant, typing style, and font variation
- **Font Size Scaling** - Scale factors, limits, and system font scale integration
- **Text Decorations** - Underline, shadow, outline, line-through, and text background color
- **Signals and Events** - TextChanged, MaximumLengthReached, CursorPositionChanged, Selection signals, and InputRejected

All code examples are grounded in the actual sample files (`text-input-field-example.cpp`, `text-example.cpp`, `text-scale-example.cpp`, `text-style-example.cpp`) and UTC tests (`utc-Dali-InputField.cpp`) from the repository.
